WEBVTT

00:03.840 --> 00:04.939
Ally!

00:04.942 --> 00:06.775
Austin!

00:06.777 --> 00:09.277
It is so good to see you,
I missed you so much.

00:09.279 --> 00:11.713
Me, too. I can't believe
it's been four months.

00:11.715 --> 00:13.015
How's school?

00:13.017 --> 00:15.450
Hard, but amazing.
How's the tour?

00:15.452 --> 00:17.386
It's been fun, but
also really lonely.

00:18.489 --> 00:21.623
And, it kinda got me thinking.

00:21.625 --> 00:22.691
About us.

00:24.327 --> 00:26.995
I didn't know at
the time, but...

00:26.997 --> 00:30.365
The day I walked in the music store
was the greatest day of my life...

00:32.168 --> 00:34.236
Because it's the day I met you.

00:36.140 --> 00:38.407
There's so much about the
future I don't know,

00:38.409 --> 00:43.645
but the one thing I'm sure of is, there's
no way I can make it without you.

00:45.215 --> 00:47.416
So,

00:47.418 --> 00:49.051
Ally Willow Dawson...

00:50.320 --> 00:52.587
Will you make me the
happiest man alive and,

00:54.090 --> 00:55.223
marry me?

00:56.492 --> 00:57.893
Austin.

01:00.430 --> 01:01.463
I can't...

01:04.333 --> 01:07.335
Believe you're really
asking me to marry you!

01:07.337 --> 01:09.671
Yes, yes, I will!

01:09.673 --> 01:10.705
Wait.

01:10.707 --> 01:12.674
That never happened.

01:12.676 --> 01:15.277
First of all, Ally's
middle name isn't Willow,

01:15.279 --> 01:17.913
and more importantly, Austin
never asked Ally to marry him.

01:17.915 --> 01:21.249
I know, but what happened
in real life is too sad.

01:21.251 --> 01:23.385
So, when I was putting
together my rockumentary,

01:23.387 --> 01:25.287
<i>the Austin and Ally story,</i>

01:25.289 --> 01:28.290
I used a little editing magic to make
it look like Austin was proposing.

01:28.292 --> 01:29.413
Here's the original footage.

01:30.726 --> 01:32.661
Whoa, what kind of bug is that?

01:34.764 --> 01:36.098
Hey, I got him.

01:37.100 --> 01:38.633
Come on. Touch him, he's fuzzy.

01:38.635 --> 01:41.203
Austin, I can't...

01:41.205 --> 01:42.337
Even look at it.

01:43.539 --> 01:45.240
Ew! Ew!

01:45.242 --> 01:46.608
Gross!

01:48.412 --> 01:50.545
No audience wants to see
what really happened.

01:50.547 --> 01:52.581
You mean that Austin and
Ally actually broke up

01:52.583 --> 01:54.416
and haven't talked to
each other in years?

01:54.418 --> 01:56.952
Uh, yeah. I can't end
my movie like that.

01:56.954 --> 01:58.453
It's all so sad.

01:58.455 --> 02:00.088
You know, Ally's coming
home this weekend,

02:00.090 --> 02:02.457
and I tried to talk her into
going to Austin's show with us,

02:02.459 --> 02:04.726
she said she doesn't
even want to see him.

02:04.728 --> 02:07.496
Austin said he doesn't
want to see her either.

02:07.498 --> 02:10.465
It's so weird that after all they've
been through they can't even be friends.

02:10.467 --> 02:11.500
Tell me about it.

02:11.502 --> 02:13.401
We're friends and
we hate each other.

02:13.403 --> 02:15.470
I know, I hate you so much.

02:18.623 --> 02:21.143
I just know that if we can get
Austin and Ally in the same room,

02:21.145 --> 02:22.777
once they see each other,

02:22.779 --> 02:25.299
everything will be fine and we can
all go back to being friends.

02:26.415 --> 02:28.650
I think I know
just how to do it.

02:28.652 --> 02:30.485
Wait a sec.

02:30.487 --> 02:33.522
Is your plan an elaborate scheme that
involves lying, trickery and deceit?

02:33.524 --> 02:35.190
Of course.

02:35.192 --> 02:36.358
Then count me in!

02:36.360 --> 02:37.492
Whoo!

